  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Nosocomial Infection</measure>
    <time_frame>within the first 30 day after surgery</time_frame>
    <description>Infection rate referred to the rate of nosocomial infection, including pneumonia, central line infection, surgical wound infection, deep sternal wound infection, urinary tract infection, and sepsis. Infections were defined according to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) definitions, occurring within 30 days postoperative cardiac surgery.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
